<Base title="Year on the Protests — Michalina Sablik">
  <div class="container page-content">
    <h1>Year on the Protests</h1>
    <p class="exhibition-detail-venue">Warsaw | 2021</p>
    <div class="exhibition-detail-body">
      <p>Outdoor exhibition of documentary photography presented during the Month of Photography. Documents 2020 protests across Poland, including those by women, the LGBTQ+ community, climate activists, Black Lives Matter supporters, entrepreneurs, unions, farmers, and citizens.</p>
      <p>Photographers stood at the forefront of these protests, often risking exposure to infection or aggression from the police, documenting events as they unfolded.</p>
      <p>The exhibition highlights how protest photographs function as activism themselves, gaining viral potential on social media.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="exhibition-detail-credits">
      <p><strong>Photographers:</strong> Karol Grygoruk, Grzegorz Wełnicki, Agata Grzybowska, Agata Kubis, Michalina Kuczyńska, Rafał Milach, Joanna Musiał, Dawid Zieliński, Edka Jarząb</p>
      <p><strong>Archive:</strong> Public Protests Archive / RATS Agency</p>
      <p><strong>Curators:</strong> Kaja Werbanowska, Michalina Sablik</p>
      <p><strong>Partners:</strong> Promocyjna Gallery, Staromiejski Dom Kultury in Warsaw</p>
    </div>
    <div class="exhibition-gallery" style="margin-top: 2.5rem; display: grid; gap: 1rem;">
